               <p>627. 
               
                  <persName id="t17900915-37-defend388" type="defendantName">
                     FRANCIS 
                     FONTON
                  <interp inst="t17900915-37-defend388" type="surname" value="FONTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17900915-37-defend388" type="given" value="FRANCIS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17900915-37-defend388" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted, for <rs id="t17900915-37-off193" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17900915-37-off193" type="offenceCategory" value="deception"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17900915-37-off193" type="offenceSubcategory" value="forgery"></interp>
               that he, on the <rs id="t17900915-37-cd194" type="crimeDate">8th of May, 1789</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17900915-37-off193 t17900915-37-cd194"></join>, in the parish of <placeName id="t17900915-37-crimeloc195">St. Christopher-le-Stocks</placeName>
                     <interp inst="t17900915-37-crimeloc195" type="placeName" value="St. Christopher-le-Stocks"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17900915-37-crimeloc195" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                     <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17900915-37-off193 t17900915-37-crimeloc195"></join>, feloniously did falsely make, forge, and counterfeit, and cause and procure to be falsely made, forged, and counterfeited, and willingly act and assist in the false making, forging, and counterfeiting a certain receipt for money, with the name J. Pierce thereto subscribed, bearing date the said 8th of May
            </rs>; and which said false, forged, and counterfeited receipt is as follows:</p>
               <p>"50 l.</p>
               <p>"four per cent. annuities, consolidated,</p>
               <p>"April 6th, 1780. Received this 8th day</p>
               <p>"of May, 1789, of 
